705170f-a.text:
Junius Street, between East New York and Liberty Aves., showing at the right the Lutheran Hospital at the S.W. corner of East New York Ave., and Junius Street. At the left, is the Freed-Eiseman Radio Corp., at the N.E. corner of Junius Street and Liberty Ave. In the foreground is a section of the Long Island R.R. tracks.

April 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704062f-b.text:
1. East New York Ave. (right), north side, east of Pacific Street to Atlantic Ave., showing also the Long Island R.R. elevated and the Atlantic Ave. station. Shown on the left, are buildings on Pacific Street, which at this
point becomes East New York Ave.
August 110, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
c. East New York Ave., Pacific St. to Atlantic Ave. Neg. A-182
P.L. Sperr  July 24, 1941
